cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.NI, cs.AI, cs.SI 

This paper deals with anomaly detection in cyber networks using machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also uses Robust Principal Component Analysis (RPCA) as a method, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with network packet capture data, which falls under the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to detect anomalies, which falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with cyber-network attacks, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
